dpaa1: true-ZC RX reprogram-WRITE + Recover-redirect (M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 4b)

The INSEPARABLE productive pair that turns DPAA1 AF_XDP RX from copy-mode into
true zero-copy (spec dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 6.1.16). Both halves
MUST land together: firing either alone guarantees the sec 6.1.8 hardware crash
class (FMan DMAs into XSK chunks that build_skb() consumes as page-pool pages ->
xp_alloc free-list corruption / dcache_clean_poc fault / soft-lockup).

Three-mechanism true-ZC RX (spec sec 6.1.7):

  1. Recognise -- the FD's bpid equals priv->xsk_bpid[band] (the FD came out of
     the dedicated XSK BMan pool). Already observable since patch 0093
     (xsk_zc_eligible) / 0094 (xsk_zc_rx_armed); productive recognition is the
     `if (fd->bpid != priv->xsk_bpid[band]) return false;` gate in the rx_hook.

  2. Recover -- turn the bare chunk DMA cookie qm_fd_addr(fd) back into its
     originating struct xdp_buff. Kernel 6.18.31 has NO xsk_buff_recv() (the
     spec sec 6.1.15 prose named a non-existent API), so this patch consumes the
     0103a reverse-map infrastructure: a per-band sorted dma_addr_t -> head-index
     bsearch array (dpaa_xsk_build_dma_index, built at attach after
     xsk_pool_dma_map) + a flat head-index -> xdp_buff* record array
     (dpaa_xsk_chunk_record, populated at every FILL-release in the attach seed
     loop and napi_refill). Design A: keyed by the XSK pool head-index
     (xskb - pool->heads), correct for BOTH aligned-contiguous AND fragmented
     UMEMs (no subtract+shift contiguity assumption).

  3. reProgram (the hardware-risky half) -- at attach, point the live FMan RX
     port's primary BMan pool from the kernel page-pool BPID (priv->dpaa_bp->bpid)
     at the dedicated XSK pool BPID (priv->xsk_bpid[queue_id]) via
     fman_port_disable(rxp) -> fman_port_set_rx_bpool(rxp, old, new) (0102
     exported it EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL) -> fman_port_enable(rxp). After this write,
     FDs start carrying the XSK bpid and the rx_hook Recovers+redirects them.

rx_hook flow (af_xdp_pool_rx_hook, dispatched from rx_default_dqrr via
priv->qmgmt_ops->rx_hook, model = tx_conf_zc): Recognise (bpid match) -> Recover
(dpaa_xsk_chunk_head_from_dma bsearch + dpaa_xsk_chunk_lookup) ->
xsk_buff_set_size + xsk_buff_dma_sync_for_cpu -> bpf_prog_run_xdp ->
xdp_do_redirect into the XSKMAP (bumps xsk_zc_rx_redirect, the 22nd xsk_*
counter). Any miss at any step (no reverse-map hit, no XDP prog, redirect
failure, XDP_PASS/TX/ABORTED) falls back to the unchanged skbuf path by
returning false -- NEVER frees or double-handles the chunk.

Byte-identical to mainline on default/vpp: the af_xdp_pool attach path is only
reached on XDP_ZEROCOPY bind (never on default flavor), and until the reprogram
write runs no FD ever carries the XSK bpid so the rx_hook returns false for every
frame. detach (patch 0076) frees both 0103a/0103b reverse-map arrays.

Entry gate (spec sec 6.1.12) DUT-MET before authoring: xsk_zc_rx_armed=2,
xsk_fill_guard_block=0 under 30s load.

